Preheat your #oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Pop the @British Cumberland sausages{4} onto a #baking tray{}.

When the oven is hot, bake the sausages on the middle shelf of your #oven until golden brown and cooked through, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. The sausages are cooked when they are no longer pink in the middle.

Pour the @water{240%ml} for the couscous and half the @chicken stock paste{15%g} into a #saucepan and bring to the boil.

When boiling, remove from the heat, stir in the @couscous{120%g} and pop a lid on the #pot. Leave to the side for ~{8-10%minutes} or until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, when the sausages have baked for ~{10%minutes}, turn them and add the pepper to the baking tray. Drizzle with @oil{a drizzle} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast for the remaining time, ~{10-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{a drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the onion and cook until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Stir in the garlic and @harissa paste{50%g}. Cook, stirring, for ~{1%minute}.

Pour in the @water{75%ml} for the sauce, @tomato passata{1%jar} and remaining chicken stock paste.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, stir in the @sugar{1/2%tsp}, then bring to the boil.

Reduce the heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, until the sauce has reduced by half, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{15%g} (stalks and all).

Once the couscous is ready, fluff it up with a #fork and stir in a drizzle of @olive oil{a drizzle} and half the parsley. Taste and season again if needed.

Once the peppers are roasted, stir them into the harissa sauce, then taste and season if needed.

When ready, share the couscous between your #bowls{} and top with the sausages.

Spoon over the harissa tomato sauce, then sprinkle over the @toasted flaked almonds{15%g} and remaining parsley to finish. Enjoy!